RTL-BenchLS dual-licensing summary
==================================

The RTL-BenchLS release is split into two parts under two licenses:

1. **Benchmark datasets** (everything under `data/` and `results/`) are
   released under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License
   (CC-BY-4.0).
   Full text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode

2. **Evaluation framework and example code** (everything else, including the
   `rtlbenchls/` Python package, the `scripts/` directory, the per-task
   examples under `tasks/`, and the `docs/` content) is released under the
   MIT License (below).

Some designs included in the dataset were derived from upstream open-source
projects (e.g., NVDLA, OpenC910, HummingBird E200, picorv32, lowRISC ibex,
black-parrot). Each retained design carries its original upstream license in
the `sources.json` field of its JSONL record. CC-BY-4.0 applies only to
RTL-BenchLS' compilation, curation, and metadata of these designs; the
designs themselves remain under their respective upstream licenses.

When citing RTL-BenchLS, use the BibTeX entry in the project README.


